lib_jobs.title: Adding a route for NCIP renewal for alma

comments.body: After some digging, it looks like this is caused by the public files directory, where files uploaded by the user are stored, is not owned by the correct user.  When I recursively changed ownership of that directory inside the OJS installation to the correct user, this worked.  I'll move this ticket over to princeton_ansible to be worked on.
Issue moved to [pulibrary/princeton_ansible #2734](https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/2734) via [**ZenHub**](https://www.zenhub.com/)

I ran this on catalog-qa it seems to have worked.
Command to set qa to read only mode:
```
ansible-playbook -e "orangelight_hosts=orangelight_alma_qa" -e "@group_vars/orangelight/alma_qa.yml" -e "ol_read_only_mode=true" playbooks/orangelight_toggle_readonly.yml
```

actual rake command to run the migration
```
rake orangelight:migration:netids
```

Command to set qa to turn off read only mode:
```
ansible-playbook -e "orangelight_hosts=orangelight_alma_qa" -e "@group_vars/orangelight/alma_qa.yml" -e "ol_read_only_mode=false" playbooks/orangelight_toggle_readonly.yml
```

I'll plan to merge and run this 9/9 during the maintenance window.

Note that it will require updating our solr config. I will update this ticket to reflect that.
